1
00:00:04,405 --> 00:00:06,841
(Minseok) ⟨I was raised by a Korean chaebol family→

2
00:00:06,907 --> 00:00:09,343
I came to Japan and fell in love with Momoko ⟩

3
00:00:09,410 --> 00:00:10,845
I like it.

4
00:00:10,911 --> 00:00:13,848
⟨but…⟩

5
00:00:13,914 --> 00:00:17,351
⟨I was stabbed by my mother, who hated me, and I was seriously injured to the point of death→

6
00:00:17,418 --> 00:00:21,355
Miraculously, he survived after receiving an organ transplant.

7
00:00:21,422 --> 00:00:22,857
⟨At times like that...⟩

8
00:00:22,923 --> 00:00:24,358
(Excellent) Photo.

9
00:00:24,425 --> 00:00:26,360
(Takuto) The person who transplanted organs to Minchok was →

10
00:00:26,427 --> 00:00:28,362
It was my father.

11
00:00:28,429 --> 00:00:31,365
(Minseok) ⟨I learned that my biological father, who was supposed to be dead, was still alive⟩

12
00:00:31,432 --> 00:00:33,868
I'm Kim Min-seok.

13
00:00:33,934 --> 00:00:35,870
(Doctor) The paralysis is becoming fixed →

14
00:00:35,936 --> 00:00:38,873
Recovery of walking may be difficult.

15
00:00:38,939 --> 00:00:40,875
(Minseok) When I meet Momoko-san →

16
00:00:40,941 --> 00:00:42,877
All I can think of is what I can't do →

17
00:00:42,943 --> 00:00:45,880
It may cause trouble.

18
00:00:45,946 --> 00:00:48,883
(Momoko) I don't want to be separated from Minseok-san.

19
00:00:48,949 --> 00:00:51,886
(Minseok) I can't stand myself.

20
00:00:51,952 --> 00:00:55,389
⟨I gave up on living with Momoko-san→

21
00:00:55,456 --> 00:00:57,958
I returned to Korea⟩

22
00:01:25,419 --> 00:01:30,424
>> Korean

23
00:02:00,955 --> 00:02:02,957
(sound of door closing)

24
00:02:21,909 --> 00:02:27,848
(Yuu) [Teru: You can't give up on what you really want]

25
00:02:27,915 --> 00:02:30,851
(Momoko) [There are words that I have always cherished]

26
00:02:30,918 --> 00:02:34,855
[“There is no tree that will not fall after being cut 10 times”]

27
00:02:34,922 --> 00:02:59,446
♪～

28
00:03:04,385 --> 00:03:08,722
(Kazami) Has everyone taken their seats? (Children) Yes!

29
00:03:08,789 --> 00:03:13,561
(Kazami) Now, let's eat! (Children) Itadakimasu!

30
00:03:16,397 --> 00:03:17,831
(Takuto) Wow!

31
00:03:17,898 --> 00:03:20,334
(Momoko) Takuto You've always loved chicken rice.

32
00:03:20,401 --> 00:03:23,837
(Takuto) This simple ketchup taste is irresistible.

33
00:03:23,904 --> 00:03:25,839
Hey? (Yusuke) Yeah!

34
00:03:25,906 --> 00:03:27,341
(Momoko) Ah!

35
00:03:27,408 --> 00:03:29,843
(Takuto) What happened? (Kazami) What happened?

36
00:03:29,910 --> 00:03:33,347
(Momoko) I forgot! Wait a minute, everyone, don't eat yet!

37
00:03:33,414 --> 00:03:35,849
This this this.

38
00:03:35,916 --> 00:03:37,351
flag!

39
00:03:37,418 --> 00:03:39,353
(Takuto) Ah!

40
00:03:39,420 --> 00:03:41,355
(Momoko) It was chicken rice, so I prepared it.

41
00:03:41,422 --> 00:03:43,357
(Children) Yay!

42
00:03:43,424 --> 00:03:45,859
(Mika) I thought something was missing.

43
00:03:45,926 --> 00:03:47,861
(Chica) Wow!

44
00:03:47,928 --> 00:03:49,863
(Momoko) Yes, please. >> Good, Momo-chan.

45
00:03:49,930 --> 00:03:51,865
Highest!

46
00:03:51,932 --> 00:03:54,368
amazing! (Momoko) Yes, Takuto too.

47
00:03:54,435 --> 00:03:55,869
(Takuto) Amazing!

48
00:03:55,936 --> 00:03:57,871
(Momoko) Yes, please go ahead.

49
00:03:57,938 --> 00:03:59,940
(Tatsuru) Komawo!

50
00:04:01,442 --> 00:04:03,310
"Komawo" in Korean →

51
00:04:03,377 --> 00:04:05,813
Does it mean "thank you"?

52
00:04:05,879 --> 00:04:07,815
(Momoko) Ah... yeah.

53
00:04:07,881 --> 00:04:10,317
(Tatsuru) Minseok told me!

54
00:04:10,384 --> 00:04:13,821
(Children) Komawo!

55
00:04:13,887 --> 00:04:16,824
(Chica) Hey, when will Minseok come back?

56
00:04:16,890 --> 00:04:20,828
(Haru) Hey, when? (Children) When?

57
00:04:20,894 --> 00:04:22,830
(Momoko) Um...｡

58
00:04:22,896 --> 00:04:26,834
(Takuto) What? You guys have me, right? Isn't it fun?

59
00:04:26,900 --> 00:04:29,336
>> Well, Takuto is fun though.

60
00:04:29,403 --> 00:04:32,906
(Takuto) No, what does "mo" mean? "Takuto too".

61
00:04:51,425 --> 00:04:53,861
(Momoko) Takuto! I was here.

62
00:04:53,927 --> 00:04:55,863
Yusuke is going to become a millionaire.

63
00:04:55,929 --> 00:04:59,867
(Takuto) Ah... I suddenly got an offer to appear on TV.

64
00:04:59,933 --> 00:05:01,869
If you contact me, I'll be right back.

65
00:05:01,935 --> 00:05:03,871
(Momoko) Yeah, hurry up.

66
00:05:08,876 --> 00:05:11,812
(Takuto) What are you doing, Minchok?

67
00:05:11,879 --> 00:05:18,819
📱(Ring tone)

68
00:05:18,886 --> 00:05:22,823
(Natsume) Ah... Deputy Manager: I can't connect.

69
00:05:22,890 --> 00:05:25,325
(Mizushima) I'm the former deputy manager.

70
00:05:25,392 --> 00:05:27,327
｢Culture Experience Plan｣→

71
00:05:27,394 --> 00:05:29,830
I just wanted to tell you that it was very popular.

72
00:05:29,897 --> 00:05:32,833
Reservations are steadily increasing from local customers.

73
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:34,835
Sigh…｡

74
00:05:34,902 --> 00:05:39,339
Even though I went home with a big offer, I still haven't returned to work.

75
00:05:39,406 --> 00:05:43,343
Hey manager. >> I need you to come back soon→

76
00:05:43,410 --> 00:05:47,915
The future of Hang Geum depends on that person.

77
00:05:53,420 --> 00:05:57,357
I'll be with you today.

78
00:05:57,424 --> 00:05:59,860
Are you coming?

79
00:05:59,927 --> 00:06:12,873
♪～

80
00:06:22,883 --> 00:06:28,322
(Kyoko) When I was little, this was a treasure.

81
00:06:28,389 --> 00:06:31,825
(Momoko) Sister, you always gave me this.

82
00:06:31,892 --> 00:06:33,827
>> Is that so?

83
00:06:33,894 --> 00:06:36,830
(Momoko) That's right.

84
00:06:36,897 --> 00:06:39,333
(Monitor) And the next country is →

85
00:06:39,399 --> 00:06:41,835
Next door is Seoul, South Korea.

86
00:06:41,902 --> 00:06:47,841
(Monitor) Popular sweets that are currently becoming a hot topic among young people in Seoul →

87
00:06:47,908 --> 00:06:49,843
This butter tok.

88
00:06:49,910 --> 00:06:52,846
(Momoko) Wow, that looks delicious.

89
00:06:52,913 --> 00:06:56,350
I like the popular sweet butter took.

90
00:06:56,416 --> 00:06:59,353
(Monitor) The inside is surprisingly chewy.

91
00:06:59,419 --> 00:07:01,922
(Momoko) Yeah, it looks like some kind of bread. It looks delicious.

92
00:07:03,857 --> 00:07:05,859
(Takuto) Nice to meet you. >> Yes.

93
00:07:07,861 --> 00:07:09,296
(Takuto) Ah.

94
00:07:09,363 --> 00:07:12,800
>> Ah, teacher.

95
00:07:12,866 --> 00:07:14,301
(Takuto) Hello.

96
00:07:14,368 --> 00:07:16,804
>> Thank you very much for your help in that section.

97
00:07:16,870 --> 00:07:18,806
(Takuto) No. How are you feeling after that?

98
00:07:18,872 --> 00:07:20,307
>> No problem.

99
00:07:20,374 --> 00:07:23,310
(Takuto) I see. Good.

100
00:07:23,377 --> 00:07:25,813
>> That...

101
00:07:25,879 --> 00:07:27,314
(Takuto) Yes.

102
00:07:27,381 --> 00:07:32,386
>> Teru… No, how is Minseok doing?

103
00:07:33,887 --> 00:07:37,324
(Takuto) Actually, I went back to Korea.

104
00:07:37,391 --> 00:07:38,826
>> Huh?

105
00:07:38,892 --> 00:07:43,831
(Takuto) He said he would help out at the head office while undergoing rehabilitation in Korea.

106
00:07:43,897 --> 00:07:47,835
>> But what about my job...?

107
00:07:47,901 --> 00:07:49,903
(Takuto) Apparently he quit.

108
00:07:51,405 --> 00:07:54,842
>> Oh... Minseok is alone?

109
00:07:54,908 --> 00:07:59,346
(Takuto) No, it seems like he lives with his brother over there.

110
00:07:59,413 --> 00:08:01,849
>> Is that so?

111
00:08:01,915 --> 00:08:05,285
Ah, have you contacted me?

112
00:08:05,352 --> 00:08:09,289
(Takuto) That's... I've been in touch with you, though.→

113
00:08:09,356 --> 00:08:12,292
I haven't been able to get a reply.

114
00:08:12,359 --> 00:08:14,361
>> Is that so?

115
00:08:15,863 --> 00:08:18,365
(Takuto) I feel bad about something.

116
00:08:19,867 --> 00:08:22,870
I finally found something important.

117
00:08:28,375 --> 00:08:30,377
(Takuto) Sorry for something.

118
00:08:31,879 --> 00:08:34,882
>> Ah, teacher.

119
00:08:37,885 --> 00:08:40,888
Korean

120
00:08:49,897 --> 00:08:53,400
(Minseok) Ah ha ha...｡

121
00:08:58,405 --> 00:09:01,842
(Minseok) Hahaha...｡

122
00:09:01,909 --> 00:09:12,286
♪～

123
00:09:12,352 --> 00:09:13,787
(Minseok) Ah.

124
00:09:13,854 --> 00:09:17,858
Ah...

125
00:09:19,359 --> 00:09:21,361
Ah.

126
00:09:21,428 --> 00:10:08,275
Korean

127
00:10:08,408 --> 00:10:26,426
♪～

128
00:10:26,093 --> 00:10:47,781
Korean

129
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:01,962
>> \Momoko-san/

130
00:11:04,898 --> 00:11:07,334
(Momoko) Eri-san.

131
00:11:07,401 --> 00:11:09,336
(Eri) Sorry for contacting you so suddenly.

132
00:11:09,403 --> 00:11:10,837
(Momoko) No, not at all.

133
00:11:10,904 --> 00:11:13,840
>> I'll be leaving Japan for a little longer this time →

134
00:11:13,907 --> 00:11:16,343
I really want to meet you before that.

135
00:11:16,410 --> 00:11:18,845
(Momoko) Huh? Is that so? >>Yes.

136
00:11:18,912 --> 00:11:21,348
You know →

137
00:11:21,415 --> 00:11:26,353
I tried interacting with the common people at that clinic...

138
00:11:26,420 --> 00:11:28,855
(Momoko) Hehe, common people.

139
00:11:28,922 --> 00:11:31,858
>> Everyone feels warm and healed →

140
00:11:31,925 --> 00:11:35,862
I thought it was really cool to live like you.

141
00:11:35,929 --> 00:11:37,864
(Momoko) Huh?

142
00:11:37,931 --> 00:11:42,369
>> When you smile, everyone becomes brighter, right?

143
00:11:42,436 --> 00:11:45,372
I feel like it's okay somehow.

144
00:11:45,439 --> 00:11:48,442
I think that's amazing.

145
00:11:50,444 --> 00:11:54,381
I was looking for someone who would make me shine →

146
00:11:54,448 --> 00:11:57,384
I'm looking at you→

147
00:11:57,451 --> 00:12:00,454
I realized that all I need to do is shine.

148
00:12:02,456 --> 00:12:05,325
(Momoko) No, that's not me...｡

149
00:12:05,392 --> 00:12:07,327
>> Hey Momoko-san.

150
00:12:07,394 --> 00:12:11,898
Try being selfish like me once in a while.

151
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:16,837
If you want something, definitely go get it.

152
00:12:16,903 --> 00:12:21,408
No matter what you do, make sure you don't have any regrets later.

153
00:12:27,414 --> 00:12:29,916
Well then, how are you?

154
00:12:31,418 --> 00:12:33,420
(Momoko) Eri-san too.

155
00:12:38,425 --> 00:12:40,427
(Momoko) Thank you!

156
00:12:48,935 --> 00:12:53,373
>> Oh my, what's wrong with this?

157
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:56,877
I was thinking about something when I bumped into you.

158
00:12:56,943 --> 00:12:59,379
Oh my, hehe.

159
00:12:59,446 --> 00:13:04,317
Well, it's just a little swollen, so I'll give you a compress.

160
00:13:04,384 --> 00:13:06,319
thank you.

161
00:13:06,386 --> 00:13:08,822
Ah, that's right, An-chan.

162
00:13:08,889 --> 00:13:10,891
Are you hungry?

163
00:13:12,392 --> 00:13:15,829
(Kyoko) I'll eat it. (Kazami) I'll eat it.

164
00:13:15,896 --> 00:13:20,333
Today, Momo-chan and Mika-chan are outside all the time →

165
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:23,336
I almost had some left over.

166
00:13:23,403 --> 00:13:25,338
delicious.

167
00:13:25,405 --> 00:13:29,342
Yeah, eat a lot.

168
00:13:29,409 --> 00:13:32,846
I used to make this a lot.

169
00:13:32,913 --> 00:13:36,349
Mr. Oinari, was it your favorite food?

170
00:13:36,416 --> 00:13:39,352
It was Momoko's favorite food.

171
00:13:39,419 --> 00:13:41,922
Ah, I see. >> Yes.

172
00:13:43,924 --> 00:13:46,359
Hey An-chan.

173
00:13:46,426 --> 00:13:52,365
An-chan was always a big sister no matter where she was.

174
00:13:52,432 --> 00:13:57,871
Here too, I always take care of small children →

175
00:13:57,938 --> 00:14:01,441
She's a big sister you can always rely on.

176
00:14:03,376 --> 00:14:07,881
Thank you very much for your hard work.

177
00:14:16,890 --> 00:14:18,325
Dean.

178
00:14:18,391 --> 00:14:19,893
yeah?

179
00:14:21,394 --> 00:14:24,331
I….

180
00:14:24,397 --> 00:14:28,335
When Momoko is with Minseok →

181
00:14:28,401 --> 00:14:30,837
I'm afraid you'll have a hard time →

182
00:14:30,904 --> 00:14:33,907
I've been worried for a long time.

183
00:14:36,409 --> 00:14:38,912
that's why….

184
00:14:41,414 --> 00:14:47,354
(Kyoko) I found out that Momoko and Minseok broke up →

185
00:14:47,420 --> 00:14:50,924
Somehow I felt relieved.

186
00:14:54,928 --> 00:14:57,430
I'm the worst.

187
00:15:03,370 --> 00:15:08,375
But Momoko hasn't been able to smile properly since then.

188
00:15:14,881 --> 00:15:18,318
(Kazami) Momo-chan →

189
00:15:18,385 --> 00:15:24,324
When I said, ``I really want to protect the children's cafeteria''→

190
00:15:24,391 --> 00:15:27,827
I said it.

191
00:15:27,894 --> 00:15:34,334
``It's tough to protect this place,'' he said.

192
00:15:34,401 --> 00:15:36,336
Then Momo-chan →

193
00:15:36,403 --> 00:15:41,408
"It's difficult, but it's important," he said.

194
00:15:44,911 --> 00:15:50,850
(Kazami) No matter how difficult things may be for Momo-chan→

195
00:15:50,917 --> 00:15:56,423
I'm sure he's a strong kid who can overcome it.

196
00:15:59,426 --> 00:16:01,861
(Kazami) That's →

197
00:16:01,928 --> 00:16:04,364
Thanks to An-chan.

198
00:16:06,866 --> 00:16:09,803
Because An-chan was there →

199
00:16:09,869 --> 00:16:13,306
Momo-chan is here now.

200
00:16:13,373 --> 00:16:38,331
♪～

201
00:16:38,398 --> 00:16:40,400
Korean

202
00:16:57,350 --> 00:17:10,430
Korean

203
00:17:16,870 --> 00:17:19,239
(Momoko) I'm home. (Kyoko) Ah, welcome back Momoko.

204
00:17:19,305 --> 00:17:22,242
(Momoko) Sister, are you okay? I heard from the director that you were injured.

205
00:17:22,308 --> 00:17:24,744
Ah, this? >> Ah... it's no big deal.

206
00:17:24,811 --> 00:17:26,746
I just hit it a little.

207
00:17:26,813 --> 00:17:28,748
(Momoko) Really? >>Yes.

208
00:17:28,815 --> 00:17:31,251
Ah, but→

209
00:17:31,317 --> 00:17:36,256
Have a little fun today →

210
00:17:36,322 --> 00:17:39,759
Is this okay for dinner?

211
00:17:39,826 --> 00:17:42,762
(Momoko) [Tastes better than usual]

212
00:17:42,829 --> 00:17:46,833
(Minseok) [One dream came true]

213
00:17:49,335 --> 00:17:50,770
>> Huh?

214
00:17:50,837 --> 00:17:53,840
(Momoko) Ah, yeah, I'll leave my bag behind.

215
00:17:56,342 --> 00:17:58,344
>> Korean

216
00:18:10,857 --> 00:18:12,859
(Hisn) Hmm!

217
00:18:24,871 --> 00:18:26,873
(Minseok) Huh?

218
00:18:38,384 --> 00:18:40,820
(Momoko) I'll eat it. >> I'll eat it.

219
00:18:40,887 --> 00:18:56,302
♪～

220
00:18:56,402 --> 00:19:20,860
Korean

221
00:19:20,860 --> 00:19:33,306
♪～

222
00:19:33,373 --> 00:19:37,310
(Kyoko) It's hot! Fu~! Let it cool down a bit.

223
00:19:37,377 --> 00:19:57,330
♪～

224
00:19:57,397 --> 00:19:59,332
(Momoko) Yes, it's a plate.

225
00:19:59,399 --> 00:20:01,334
>> Huh? Haha...

226
00:20:01,401 --> 00:20:04,837
Wow, that's amazing! Ahhh...

227
00:20:04,904 --> 00:20:08,908
It's my first time seeing it. Yeah.

228
00:20:11,911 --> 00:20:16,349
Ah, this... Hey.

229
00:20:16,416 --> 00:20:19,285
(cry)

230
00:20:19,352 --> 00:20:21,788
>> Eh, what happened?

231
00:20:21,854 --> 00:20:24,791
Huh... what happened?

232
00:20:24,857 --> 00:20:26,793
(Momoko) Sorry, no...

233
00:20:26,859 --> 00:20:30,296
(cry)

234
00:20:30,363 --> 00:20:32,298
Oh no, already...

235
00:20:32,365 --> 00:20:44,310
(cry)

236
00:20:44,377 --> 00:20:47,380
>> Did Minseok tell you?

237
00:20:51,884 --> 00:20:53,820
I see.

238
00:20:53,886 --> 00:21:06,332
♪～

239
00:21:06,399 --> 00:21:08,401
I've already graduated.

240
00:21:11,404 --> 00:21:16,909
I was proactive and worried about a lot of things...

241
00:21:19,846 --> 00:21:23,850
That older sister has already graduated!

242
00:21:30,857 --> 00:21:33,292
I haven't been able to smile properly lately.

243
00:21:33,359 --> 00:21:39,799
(cry)

244
00:21:39,866 --> 00:21:46,305
>> No matter where Momoko is and who she is with from now on →

245
00:21:46,372 --> 00:21:49,375
Momoko is definitely fine.

246
00:21:52,879 --> 00:21:55,815
For Momoko →

247
00:21:55,882 --> 00:21:59,385
I want you to live a life that makes you laugh from the bottom of your heart.

248
00:22:01,888 --> 00:22:04,390
(Momoko) Big sister...

249
00:22:11,898 --> 00:22:13,833
>> Eh...｡

250
00:22:13,900 --> 00:22:22,342
(cry)

251
00:22:32,351 --> 00:22:56,375
♪～

252
00:22:57,877 --> 00:23:00,380
>> Sorry for coming so suddenly.

253
00:23:02,381 --> 00:23:05,318
It surprised me.

254
00:23:05,384 --> 00:23:07,820
(Minseok) Why are you here?

255
00:23:07,887 --> 00:23:10,323
>>I asked Mr. Takuto.

256
00:23:10,390 --> 00:23:12,325
There's something I really want to talk about.

257
00:23:12,391 --> 00:23:15,895
Could you give me just a little bit of time?

258
00:23:25,905 --> 00:23:28,841
It's been 20 years since I came to Seoul.

259
00:23:28,908 --> 00:23:30,910
(Minseok) What is the story?

260
00:23:36,916 --> 00:23:41,854
